%20weather%20degrades%20the%20accuracy%20of%20navigation%20systems%20and%20hampers%20military%20operations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClimate%20change%20has%20made%20weather%20patterns%20more%20erratic%20and%20harder%20to%20forecast.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20makes%20it%20harder%20for%20commanders%20to%20plan%20missions%20and%20prepare%20for%20weather%20effects.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20extreme%20weather%20is%20scrambling%20the%20high-tech%20systems%20that%20have%20given%20the%20US%20military%20its%20edge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20severe%20weather%20can%20degrade%20navigation%20systems%20such%20as%20GPS%20and%20sensors%20on%20precision-guided%20munitions.%20Heavy%20rain%20ground%20aircraft%20and%20drones%2C%20intense%20heat%20exhausts%20troops%2C%20dust%20storms%20gum%20up%20tank%20engines%2C%20and%20storms%20damage%20ships%20at%20sea.%20Smoke%20and%20sandstorms%20blind%20aerial%20drones.%20Commanders%20and%20troops%20need%20to%20have%20a%20good%20idea%20of%20what%20the%20weather%20will%20be%20like%20the%20next%20day%20or%20the%20next%20month%20%E2%80%94%20forecasts%20that%20are%20getting%20fouled%20by%20the%20growing%20unpredictability%20of%20weather%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReliably%20forecasting%20extreme%20weather's%20frequency%20and%20intensity%20to%20inform%20strategy%20is%20perhaps%20the%20most%20important%20challenge%20for%20the%20US%20and%20allied%20militaries%20to%20adapt%20to%20or%20mitigate%20a%20changing%20climate%2C%20because%20it%20is%20imperative%20that%20operations%20and%20campaigns%20are%20feasible%20meteorologically%2C%26quot%3B%20warned%20James%20Regens%20in%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Frusi-journal%2Fextreme-weather-risk-military-operations-changing-climate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eessay%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20a%20British%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnexpected%20weather%20has%20always%20frustrated%20the%20best-laid%20plans%20of%20commanders.%20Had%20rain%20not%20turned%20the%20ground%20muddy%20the%20night%20before%20the%20battle%2C%20Napoleon%20might%20have%20been%20able%20to%20move%20up%20his%20artillery%20and%20win%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.ametsoc.org%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fbams%2F74%2F3%2F1520-0477_1993_074_0413_ghetws_2_0_co_2.xml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWaterloo%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Surprise%20dust%20storms%20crippled%20helicopters%20in%20the%20daring%20American%20operation%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.asomf.org%2Foperation-eagle-claw%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erescue%20hostages%20from%20Iran%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201980.%20And%20rain%20and%20rough%20seas%20almost%20caused%20the%20D-Day%20landings%20in%20June%201944%20to%20be%20cancelled.%20But%20in%20military%20meteorology's%20finest%20hour%2C%20sharp-eyed%20Allied%20weathermen%20were%20able%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rmets.org%2Fmetmatters%2Fhow-weather-forecast-made-history-d-day-landings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforecast%20a%20break%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20storms%20that%20the%20Germans%20didn't%20foresee%2C%20which%20allowed%20the%20invasion%20to%20achieve%20tactical%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20these%20mishaps%20reflect%20weather%2C%20which%20is%20a%20short-term%20phenomenon.%20Climate%20refers%20to%20long-term%20patterns%2C%20including%20the%20probability%20of%20severe%20weather.%20While%20climate%20change%20has%20become%20a%20highly%20politicized%20issue%2C%20there%20is%20general%20agreement%20among%20scientists%20that%20the%20Earth's%20climate%20is%20getting%20warmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Iraqi%20C-130E%20Hercules%20photographed%20during%20a%202006%20sand%20storm.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66479c2e14fb5b23cc5dee33%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Iraqi%20C-130E%20Hercules%20photographed%20during%20a%202006%20sand%20storm.%3Cp%3EStaff%20Sgt.%20Jason%20Serrit%2FUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20weather%20will%20be%20hotter%20everywhere%20all%20the%20time%2C%20but%20it%20does%20indicate%20that%20severe%20weather%20events%20%E2%80%94%20heat%2C%20rain%2C%20even%20snow%20%E2%80%94%20will%20be%20more%20intense%20when%20they%20happen.%20One%20example%20is%20California%20in%202024%2C%20which%20went%20from%20years%20of%20drought%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F19%2Fweather%2Fcalifornia-storm-rain-flooding-tuesday%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Batmospheric%20rivers%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20dumped%20massive%20amounts%20of%20rain%20that%20caused%20mudslides%20and%20damaged%20homes%20and%20roads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20can%20be%20catastrophic%20for%20farmers%20and%20people%20living%20in%20flood%20zones.%20But%20it's%20equally%20bad%20for%20militaries%2C%20especially%20those%20with%20advanced%20capabilities%20such%20as%20the%20US%20armed%20forces%2C%20which%20rely%20on%20delicate%20and%20interconnected%20systems%20that%20can%20be%20degraded%20by%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20meteorological%20information%20is%20key%20to%20the%20position%2C%20navigation%20and%20timing%20(PNT)%20systems%20that%20enable%20many%20guided%20weapons%20and%20communications%20networks%20to%20function%20and%20coordinate.%20%26quot%3BPrecision%20fires%2C%20aircraft%20flight%20operations%2C%20surface%20warship%20maneuver%2C%20ballistic%20missile%20trajectories%20and%20satellite%20launch%20windows%20to%20support%20intelligence%20collection%20and%20communications%20systems%20all%20depend%20on%20reliable%20PNT%20solutions%20grounded%20in%20meteorological%20projections%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Regens%2C%20an%20intelligence%20expert%20and%20founding%20partner%20of%20Antiphon%20Solutions%2C%20an%20Oklahoma-based%20analytics%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20puts%20a%20premium%20on%20developing%20models%20and%20technologies%20that%20can%20offer%20accurate%20short-%20and%20long-term%20weather%20forecasts%2C%20and%20do%20so%20even%20as%20scientific%20understanding%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20global%20climate%20change%20evolves.%20The%20strategic%20implications%20are%20profound.%20For%20example%2C%20knowing%20the%20rate%20at%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FNews-Stories%2FArticle%2FArticle%2F3353265%2Farctic-heating-up-literally-and-as-scene-of-strategic-competition%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArctic%20ice%20is%20melting%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20creating%20new%20shipping%20channels%20and%20uncovering%20mineral%20riches%20%E2%80%94%20is%20of%20great%20interest%20to%20many%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArctic%20warming%20creates%20a%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20homeland%20defense%20and%20national%20security%20challenge%20for%20US%20and%20allied%20decision-making%20for%20North%20America%20and%20NATO's%20northern%20flank%20in%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20Regens%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAdd%20to%20this%20mix%20the%20humanitarian%20missions%20the%20US%20military%20does%20in%20response%20to%20floods%2C%20monsoons%2C%20and%20other%20weather%20problems%2C%20and%20the%20Pentagon%20and%20NATO%20need%20to%20recognize%20the%20risk%20extreme%20weather%20in%20a%20changing%20climate%20poses%20to%20military%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Regens%20points%20to%20another%20problem%3A%20getting%20timely%20weather%20forecasts%20to%20those%20who%20need%20them.%20%26quot%3BMilitary%20forecasting%20works%20fine%20as%20long%20as%20units%20have%20secure%20network%20access%20to%20near-real%20time%20numerically%20predictive%20weather%20information%20for%20planning%20and%20executing%20missions%2C%26quot%3B%20Regens%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20tactical%20units%20on%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20or%20in%20remote%20areas%2C%20often%20lack%20the%20connectivity%20to%20receive%20weather%20reports.%20%26quot%3BNOAA%20%5Bthe%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%5D%2C%20the%20private%20sector%20and%20universities%20are%20actively%20working%20to%20improve%20global%20weather%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20Regens%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20missing%20link%20is%20compressing%20this%20capability%20into%20a%20tactical%20package%20for%20warfighters.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20requires%20a%20major%20effort%20to%20meet%20the%20requirements%20of%20tactically%20disaggregated%2C%20independently%20operating%20units%20for%20immediate%20reliable%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Regens.%20%26quot%3BOtherwise%2C%20they%20are%20going%20to%20have%20limited%20success%20firing%20highly%20lethal%20and%20expensive%20munitions%20at%20significant%20ranges.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20an%20MA%20in%20political%20science%20from%20Rutgers%20Univ.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETwitter%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fmipeck%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextreme-weather-blunts-the-us-militarys-technological-edge-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716109922000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66479b859fc063e829b280c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextreme-weather-blunts-the-us-militarys-tech