3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnickname-vs-real-name-identity-struggle-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplayground%20nicknames%3C%2Fa%3E%20I%20didn't%20like%20%E2%80%94%20Corky%20and%20Corny%20%E2%80%94%20and%20mispronunciations%20by%20people%20who%20honestly%20had%20no%20idea%20where%20to%20start%20%E2%80%94%20Coteny%2C%20Curtney%2C%20or%20Courtnae.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e37d4bf-4bc3-4c66-9cd1-d17e1ea773f7%5C%22%3EMy%20mom%20wanted%20an%20original%20name%20for%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-changed-name-after-mom-died-dad-got-dementia-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMy%20mother%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20her%20siblings%20had%20all%20been%20named%20after%20her%20dad's%20friends%2C%20and%20she'd%20wanted%20something%20original%20for%20me.%20Around%20the%20time%20I%20was%20born%2C%20she%20saw%20that%20movie%20industry%20exec%20Jack%20Valenti%20had%20named%20his%20daughter%20Courtenay%20and%20liked%20the%20sound%20and%20spelling%20of%20it.%20My%20dad%20preferred%20Lisa%2C%20but%20the%20closest%20he%20got%20was%20choosing%20my%20middle%20name%2C%20Lynn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20I've%20used%20the%20name%20Lisa%20many%20times%20over%20the%20years%20when%20placing%20an%20order%20or%20putting%20my%20name%20on%20a%20waitlist.%20People%20understood%20right%20away%20what%20I%20was%20saying%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20spell%20or%20repeat%20it.%20Half%20the%20time%20I%20use%20my%20real%20name%2C%20the%20other%20person%20thinks%20I'm%20saying%20Britney.%20It's%20OK%2C%20I%20answer%20to%20all%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffriends-cast-first-episode-finale-2021-reunion-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BFriends%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20along%20and%20Courteney%20Cox%20became%20a%20household%20name%2C%20it%20got%20a%20bit%20easier.%20My%20name%20was%20now%20in%20the%20lexicon%20of%20popular%20culture.%20Soon%2C%20other%20Courtneys%20appeared%3A%20singer%20Courtney%20Love%2C%20actor%20Courtney%20Thorne-Smith%2C%20and%2C%20a%20few%20years%20later%2C%20reality%20star%20Kourtney%20Kardashian.%20Now%20it's%20much%20more%20popular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f33cabfd-52db-48d8-b983-79911994f8cc%5C%22%3EStill%20people%20don't%20spell%20my%20name%20right%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20rarely%20spell%20my%20name%20right%20because%20they%20don't%20know%20if%20it%20starts%20with%20a%20C%2C%20K%2C%20or%20Q.%20I%20once%20had%20someone%20spell%20it%20as%20Quart-Knee%2C%20which%20was%20phonetically%20correct%20and%20led%20to%20my%20Facebook%20friends%20jokingly%20calling%20me%20%26quot%3BQ%26quot%3B%20for%20years%20afterward.%20I'm%20impressed%20and%20touched%20when%20someone%20takes%20the%20time%20to%20spell%20my%20name%20correctly%2C%20and%20it's%20made%20me%20hyper-aware%20of%20spelling%20others'%20names%20right.%20It's%20a%20small%20thing%20that%20makes%20a%20big%20difference.%20People%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20of%20my%20college%20friends%2C%20along%20with%20my%20Filipino%20mother-in-law%2C%20shortened%20my%20name%20both%20in%20text%20and%20aloud%20to%20just%20Court.%20I%20like%20it%20and%20consider%20it%20a%20term%20of%20endearment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20I%20always%20had%20to%20spell%20and%20repeat%20my%20name%2C%20I%20wanted%20my%20own%20kids%20to%20have%20short%2C%20simple%20ones.%20If%20I'd%20had%20a%20girl%2C%20we%20would%20have%20named%20her%20Ava%20%E2%80%94%20a%20memorable%20moniker%20using%20only%20two%20letters.%20Perhaps%20name%20complexity%20skips%20a%20generation.%20My%20sons%20both%20have%20one-syllable%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20younger%2C%20I%20didn't%20appreciate%20my%20uncommon%20name%2C%20but%20now%20I%20do.%20I%20like%20that%20it's%20a%20little%20complicated%2C%20just%20like%20me.%20I've%20only%20met%20one%20other%20person%20who%20spells%20her%20name%20like%20mine%20%E2%80%94%20another%20writer%2